

ques : Kth largest element problem

we have N scores , need the kth largest score(1 based indexing) , sorting all n score works but it is wasteful and large

Brute force : sort the entire array in descending order , return the element at k-1 index , complex : o(nlogn) due to sorting*/

brute :

optimised approach : use min heap in which we are going to keep smaller element on top.
in cpp to create min heap use priority_queue<int, vector<int>, greater<int>>*/




approach start with empty min heap , go through each of them , if heap size > k remove the smallest one(pop top)
at the end heap has exactly k largest element


ðŸ‘‰ Example:
Scores = [3, 2, 1, 5, 6, 4], K=2

Push 3 â†’ heap [3]

Push 2 â†’ heap [2,3]

Push 1 â†’ heap [1,3,2] â†’ size > 2 â†’ pop smallest â†’ heap [2,3]

Push 5 â†’ heap [2,3,5] â†’ size > 2 â†’ pop smallest â†’ heap [3,5]

Push 6 â†’ heap [3,5,6] â†’ size > 2 â†’ pop smallest â†’ heap [5,6]

Push 4 â†’ heap [4,6,5] â†’ size > 2 â†’ pop smallest â†’ heap [5,6]
Final heap = [5,6]. Top = 5 â†’ 2nd largest âœ….*/


int main() {
  
    //brute
    
    int n ;
    cin>>n;
    vector<int>a(n);
    for(int i = 0 ; i<n ; i++){
        cin>>a[i];
    }
    int k ;
    cin>>k;
    sort(a.begin(),a.end(),greater<int>()); //descedning sort
    cout<<a[k-1]<<" ";
    cout<<endl;
    //min heap : optimised version
    cout<<"Optimised sol: "<<endl;
    
    
    priority_queue<int, vector<int> , greater<int>> minheap ; //creates mean heap in cpp
    for(int x : a){
        minheap.push(x);
        if(minheap.size() > k){
            minheap.pop();
        }
    }
    cout<<minheap.top()<<" ";
    return 0;
}
